on campus. Student violations are subject to sanctions according to the  Student Disciplinary Policy .       Text     State Law vs Federal Law    Although legal in some states cannabis, a Schedule 1 controlled substance is still considered illegal by the federal government and subject to criminal charges.     Keep it off campus    The University of Illinois at Chicago prohibits the unlawful or unauthorized possession, use, distribution, dispensation, sale, or manufacture of marijuana on University property or as part of any University activity.     Don’t be on the Move    You cannot operate heavy machinery, a vehicle, or ride a bike under the influence of cannabis. A THC blood concentration of five nanograms or more per milliliter is considered driving under the influence.     Be of Age    Starting January 1, 2020, adults over 21, will be able to legally purchase cannabis for recreational use from licensed dispensaries across the state.     Impairment is a No    Please refer to the Student Disciplinary Policy for more information.     Stay Inside the State/Country    It is illegal to transport cannabis across any state or national borders.     Stay Inside the House    You can only use cannabis at home (if your landlord allows it) or on private property (if the owner allows it). Check your lease! This does not apply to Campus Housing, which is state property.     Medical Marijuana Card Use Prohibited    The prohibited use of cannabis on campus includes those who have medical marijuana cards.     Limits for Illinois Residents    • 30 grams (1 ounce) of cannabis flower • 5 grams (0.17 ounce) of cannabis concentrate • No more than 500 mg (0.017 ounce) THC contained in a cannabis infused product     Limits for Illinois Nonresidents    • 15 (0.5 ounce) grams of cannabis flower • 2.5 (0.08 ounce) grams of cannabis • No more than 250 mg (0.008 ounce) THC contained in a cannabis infused product     Grow Within the Limits    Those with medical marijuana cards, with land lord approval, can grow five plants or less at their residence. This is not allowed any where on UIC campus property, including residence halls. Non-medical marijuana card holders are not allowed to grow cannabis.         Questions?    Have questions about cannabis and its health effects? Click here to read “Drugs of Abuse” a resource guide prepared by the U.S. Drug Enforcement Administration.           Assistance    Back to main content           Academic Concerns     Academic Resources    Academic Grievances    Withdrawal    Emergencies and Absences      Health & Personal Concerns     Hospitalization & Emergencies    Mental Health    Victims of Crime and Safety Concerns    Housing Instability & Food Insecurity    Financial Concerns    Cannabis: Know the Facts      Campus Life    Faculty & Staff Resources     The Student Response Team    Behavioral Response Intervention Team      U & I Care     Meet Our Partners    Care Facts    News & Events    U & I Care Fund    U & I Care Plan                    UIC Logo        Office of the Dean of Students         DOS Offices    Career Services    Student Employment    Counseling Center    Wellness Center      For Employees    SA Human Resources    SA Technology    Leave Management    The Pulse      Safety    UIC Police    Office of Access & Equity    Contact-US    Giving         Contact   1200 West Harrison St., 3030 SSB Chicago, IL 60607  Phone: (312) 996-4857  dos@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts             UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Openings  Library  Maps  UIC Safe Mobile App  UIC Today  UI Health  Veterans Affairs        Powered by Red 2.38.0  © 2020 The Board of Trustees of the University of Illinois |  Privacy Statement    Campuses   University of Illinois System  Urbana-Champaign  Springfield      Cookie Settings                 